## Boundary contract

**Protocol/state source of truth**: `prfaq.md`, `explanation_ledger.md`,
the project decision log, and reviewed pre-registrations define the scoped
question, competing explanations, planning commitments, evidence status, and
durable state transitions. Exploratory notes may inform candidates; they do not
become claim-cited evidence until rerun or confirmed under the appropriate
claim-bearing plan.

**Project-instance artifacts**: `../../configs/`, `../../src/`,
`../../tests/`, `../../purposes/`, and `../../results/` contain concrete
universes, data paths, model definitions, parameters, implementation,
generated notebooks, and run outputs.

**Generated report snapshots**: reports under `../../results/reports/` may
summarize a run, but they do not update workstream state by themselves.
Support, reject, merge, park, or pivot only by updating
`explanation_ledger.md` and recording the transition in `../../decisions.md`
with evidence links.

Do not put active candidates, tuned parameters, current performance metrics, or trial-specific
conclusions in reusable workflow docs. Those belong in project-instance
configs, trial reports, or decision entries.

