## Workflow checklist

For an agent or user to verify the project is in good shape at any
point:

- [ ] `prfaq.md` is reviewed and status is READY
- [ ] Exploratory research and confirmatory research are labeled separately in
  run notes, tracker rows, notebooks, or result rows
- [ ] Every claim-bearing, externally shared, or terminal-decision
  high-reliability trial has a reviewed pre-registration (`prereg/PR_<id>_<slug>.md`
  status is READY before confirmatory execution)
- [ ] Before claim-bearing confirmatory execution, `PR_<id>_<slug>.md` was
  compared against the current state:
  exploratory result, data availability, assumptions, implementation
  constraints, and current question still match the PR
- [ ] Preregistered outcome reports, when produced, use
  `../../results/reports/RPT_<id>_<slug>/`. Required core files:
  `report.md`, `report.html`, `figures/`, `tables/`, and `attachments/`.
  Required core directories may be empty. Optional / situation-specific files:
  `report.pdf` and `provenance/` with `manifest.json`,
  `integrity_checks.md`, and `rerun.md`. `report.html` is the primary
  readable artifact for L2/L3 reports; `report.md` is editable source;
  `report.pdf` is optional snapshot/export. Use provenance/ for
  claim-bearing or L2/L3 reports. L2/L3 reports means claim-bearing reports
  and state-promotion or terminal-decision report packages; it is report
  package level, not analysis tier. In plain terms, report.html is the primary
  readable artifact for L2/L3 reports; report.md is editable source;
  report.pdf is optional snapshot/export.
- [ ] `explanation_ledger.md` has at least 2 competing explanations
  per active question (≥1 should be a null / artifact explanation)
- [ ] Every trial in `purposes/` has a complete Analysis section (5
  sub-fields, A0-A5 tier explicit), and preregistered outcome reports include
  Transparent Changes
- [ ] `decisions.md` records durable state transitions and claim-bearing
  material changes; ordinary run notes may stay with the tracker or trial artifact
- [ ] Report provenance or run-note convention is clear for each
  claim-bearing report package
- [ ] Selection, sweep, and failed-run records exist when they affect a
  multiple-testing or support judgment
- [ ] Report provenance records enough rerun guidance for presented evidence
  via a local run note, results row, report provenance file, or equivalent
  tracker record
- [ ] No material change from any pre-registration is unaddressed; claim-cited
  use is narrowed or rerun when the original plan no longer answers the
  intended question
- [ ] IMRAD draft started after PR/FAQ readiness (not deferred to the end)

